  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which among the following is NOT benzylic halide?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>Chlorophenylmethane</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>1-Chloro-1-phenylethane</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>2-Chloro-2-phenylpropane</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>1-Chloro-2-phenylbutane</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>In benzylic halides, halogen atom is bonded to a $\\mathrm{sp}^3$ hybridised carbon atom which is further bonded to an aromatic ring.</p>\n<p>1-Chloro-2-phenylbutane is $1^{\\circ}$ alkyl halide.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mfo8sryr/e2012818-e3a7-4d20-ad72-818699c6364b/df28ee30-93e9-11f0-a2b3-1fa2d7fb2438/file-jaoe38c1mfo8srys.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mfo8sryr/e2012818-e3a7-4d20-ad72-818699c6364b/df28ee30-93e9-11f0-a2b3-1fa2d7fb2438/file-jaoe38c1mfo8srys.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"MHT CET (PCB) 2025 9th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 1 English Explanation\">",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2025-9th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which among the following is vinylic halide?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{X}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{X}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{C} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{X}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{X}$</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>In vinylic halides, halogen atom is bonded to a $\\mathrm{sp}^2$ hybridized carbon atom of aliphatic chain.</p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n<table class=\"tg\"><thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">Compound</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">Type</th>\n  </tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{X}<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">Allylic halide</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{X}<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">Vinylic halide</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{C} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{X}<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">Haloalkyne</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{X}<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">Benzylic halide</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2025-9th-april-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which of the following compounds has highest boiling point?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>1-Bromobutane</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>1-Bromo-2-methylpropane</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>2-Bromobutane</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>2-Bromo-2-methylpropane</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>For isomeric alkyl halides boiling point decreases with increase in branching.</p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n<table class=\"tg\"><thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">Compound</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\text { Boiling point (K) }<br>$$<br></th>\n  </tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\text { 1-Bromobutane }<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">375</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\text { 1-Bromo-2-methylpropane }<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">364.1</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\text { 2-Bromobutane }<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">364</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$<br>\\text { 2-Bromo-2-methylpropane }<br>$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">346</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2025-9th-april-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
