  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Alkyl chlorides on heating with metal fluorides form alkyl fluorides. This reaction is known as\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Finkelstein reaction\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Sandmeyer's reaction\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Swartz reaction\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Saytzeff reaction"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Alkyl fluorides are prepared by heating alkyl chlorides or bromides with metal fluorides such as $\\mathrm{AgF}, \\mathrm{Hg}_2 \\mathrm{~F}_2, \\mathrm{AsF}_3, \\mathrm{SbF}_3$ etc.</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{Cl}+\\mathrm{AgF} \\longrightarrow \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{F}+\\mathrm{AgCl} \\downarrow $$</p>\n<p>The reaction is known as Swartz reaction.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which of the following compounds has highest boiling point?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " 1-Bromobutane\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " 1-Bromo-2-methylpropane\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " 2-Bromobutane\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " 2-Bromo-2-methylpropane"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Increased branching in alkyl halides reduces surface area and weakens van der Waals forces between molecules. As a result, the boiling point decreases.</p>\n<p>1-bromobutane has a linear structure, which provides larger surface area and stronger van der Waals forces than branched haloalkanes, resulting in a higher boiling point.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Identify the correct increasing order of boiling point of following compounds.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " $\\mathrm{CHBr}_3<\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{Br}_2<\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Br}<\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " $\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}<\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Br}<\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{Br}_2<\\mathrm{CHBr}_3$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Br}<\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{Br}_2<\\mathrm{CHBr}_3<\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " $\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{Br}_2<\\mathrm{CHBr}_3<\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Br}<\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Boiling point $\\propto$ Molecular mass</p>\n<p>As the number of bromine atom increases, the molecular mass of the alkyl halide increases. Therefore, the B.P of $\\mathrm{CHBr}_3$ is the highest.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
